 from humesdg one netnews jhuapl edu dave humes subject xwd segmentation fault keywords xwd x one one organization jhu applied physics laboratory lines two two i was planning to use the following pipe to move some display data to a system that has a color hardcopy unit xwd xwud display hostname zero zero i had tested it with some simple windows like the openwindows file manager and it worked fine but when i tried it with a more complex larger image the xwd part blew up with a segmentation fault i tried it without the pipe by redirecting xwd s output to a file and then used the file as input to xwud and got the same error from xwud if i had to guess it seems like it s running out of memory but this happened on a sparc one zero with six four megs one two eight meg swap space and only one user with minimal activity the file was about three mb this verion of xwd xwud was supplied with the sun openwindows three zero distribution which i believe corresponds to x one one r four any ideas thanks in advance dave humes johns hopkins university applied physics laboratory four one zero seven nine two six six five one humesdg one aplcomm jhuapl edu